## What To Stop Doing / Deprioritize

### Defer or radically scope down
- **Phase 48 (Dashboard Home Redesign)** — pause execution. The 5 plans are ready but landing a polished dashboard home doesn't move PMF. The dashboard works; it doesn't need to be "a daily-use command center" yet because most users won't open it daily — they'll open it when a lead arrives. Come back to this after PMF signals are clearer.
- **Phase 49 (Dark Mode)** — defer indefinitely. Pure polish on the wrong axis.
- **The integrated AI chat panel on the dashboard home** (part of Phase 48) — don't build this. Contractors don't want to chat with their CRM.

### Hide, don't delete
- **Invoices, estimates, accounting integrations** (Phases 33–35) — remove these from the public landing page, the pricing page feature matrix, and the primary nav. Keep the code — they're shipped, users who care can find them in `/dashboard/invoices`. But they dilute the "answer calls, book jobs" promise for first-time visitors.
- **Batch invoice review, invoice reminders, recurring invoices** — same. Great features, wrong story for the front door.
- **The in-dashboard AI chatbot assistant (Phase 37)** — keep it, but don't market it. It's a power-user thing.

### Trim from the landing page
- **The FeaturesCarousel** (8-feature showcase) — reduce to 3–4 core value pillars max ("Never miss a lead," "Book jobs automatically," "Stay in control," "Works with your calendar"). Kill the rest of the feature-card real estate.
- **The PracticalObjectionsGrid + IdentitySection + OwnerControlPullQuote + BeyondReceptionistSection** — you have 4 separate "we get you" sections. Consolidate into ONE. Pick the strongest (probably BeyondReceptionistSection's "Answering the phone is the easy part") and cut the others or tuck them below the fold under an expandable "See more" pattern.
- **The "Start My 5-Minute Setup" primary CTA** — change it. DeepSeek is right: it implies work. Swap for **"Hear Voco in Action"** (→ audio demo) as the above-the-fold CTA, and keep **"Start 14-day trial"** as the secondary / final CTA.

