## The Mental Model Shift

Every AI arrived at the same core reframing and it's worth stating plainly:

> You are not building **an AI receptionist SaaS platform.**
>
> You are building **a revenue capture machine that happens to use AI to answer calls.**

Every decision — what to build next, what to cut from the landing page, what to say in the headline, what to charge — gets easier once you accept that reframing. The product doesn't need to change much. The story does.

The contractors you're selling to aren't IT buyers. They're business owners watching leads evaporate in real time. They don't want a platform. They want the leak plugged. Everything that reinforces "we plug the leak" stays. Everything that reinforces "we are a platform" gets pushed below the fold or off the site entirely.

